# Greywater repo — line endings and diff behavior.
# Text files normalize to LF in the repository; checkout respects the platform.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Windows-only tooling that must retain CRLF (rare, but keeps batch scripts sane).
*.bat    text eol=crlf
*.cmd    text eol=crlf
*.ps1    text eol=crlf

# Source.
*.cpp    text diff=cpp
*.hpp    text diff=cpp
*.h      text diff=cpp
*.c      text diff=cpp
*.rs     text diff=rust
*.toml   text
*.cmake  text
CMakeLists.txt text

# Shader source (SPIR-V target) — compiled at build time.
*.vert   text
*.frag   text
*.comp   text
*.hlsl   text
*.glsl   text

# Markdown.
*.md     text diff=markdown

# Binary: do not touch.
*.png    binary
*.jpg    binary
*.ktx2   binary
*.spv    binary
*.dds    binary
*.mp4    binary
*.webm   binary
*.gltf   binary
*.glb    binary

# Git LFS — cooked content families produced by tools/cook/.
# audit-2026-04-20 P4.5: declare LFS patterns BEFORE the first cooked asset
# lands under /assets/, otherwise a 200 MB .gwmesh blob gets baked into the
# pack history and the repo never shrinks again.
#
# Enabling LFS requires `git lfs install` on every developer clone and a
# server-side LFS endpoint. Until we stand up GitHub LFS / Gitea LFS, the
# patterns here are declarative: they mark these extensions as `-text` +
# `filter=lfs` so that a misconfigured checkout fails loud rather than
# committing a 200 MB binary into pack history.
*.gwmesh filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.gwtex  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.gwanim filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.gwaud  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
